Argentine Stocks: Aluar Aluminio, Grupo Galicia and Ledesma Gain

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-03-18T21:03:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/argentine-stocks-aluar-aluminio-grupo-galicia-and-ledesma-gain.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4:01 p.m.  New York  time.  The Merval Index rose 0.5 percent to 3,277.87.    Aluar Aluminio Argentino SAIC (ALUA)  ,  Argentina ’s
largest aluminum producer, rose for a second day, gaining 0.2
percent to 5.32 pesos. Aluminum rose to a one-week high in  London .    Grupo Financiero Galicia SA (GGAL)   increased 0.2 percent
to 5.43 pesos and gained as much as 2.4 percent. Argentine
sovereign bonds rose, signaling higher values of banks’ fixed-
income holdings.  Ledesma SAAI (LEDE AF) rose 3.7 percent to 9.16 pesos, the
highest level in more than two weeks. The Argentine sugar
producer rose in line with sugar prices in New York, which
gained as commodity-demand concerns eased.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
